14:34.819 --> 14:36.706
Oh, I haven't even started.

14:36.721 --> 14:38.074
<i>♪ I'm the Scatman ♪</i>

14:44.644 --> 14:47.763
<i>♪ I'm the Scatman ♪</i>

15:06.483 --> 15:08.337
You can stop feeling sorry
for yourselves,

15:08.352 --> 15:10.006
because this never happened.

15:11.456 --> 15:13.109
Starting... now.

15:13.124 --> 15:14.544
Now!

15:14.559 --> 15:16.679
Now, now, now, now, now, now,
now, now, now, now, now!

15:16.687 --> 15:18.093
Aw, Stan.

15:18.157 --> 15:19.916
When I was grabbing a snack
last night,

15:19.947 --> 15:23.653
I "accidentally" knocked
that thing off the counter

15:23.953 --> 15:26.969
'cause it wasn't on my... radar.

15:27.754 --> 15:29.959
I...
Uh, uh...

15:29.974 --> 15:31.961
And I wasn't really
getting a snack.

15:31.976 --> 15:34.530
That mission was purely
to be a rascal.

15:34.601 --> 15:38.234
Although, I did reward myself
with a sleeve of saltines

15:38.290 --> 15:42.447
and four packs of Gushers.
Happy Father's Day.

15:46.829 --> 15:48.859
Hey, guys.
Uh, I know you didn't think

15:48.939 --> 15:50.995
my jokes earlier were very funny.

15:51.351 --> 15:54.531
Jokes?! What you said
was unforgivable!

15:54.609 --> 15:55.633
You can't dissect comedy!

15:55.830 --> 15:57.668
Anyway, I know you're feeling
a little down,

15:57.733 --> 16:01.263
so I made you one
of my famous apology cakes.

16:01.316 --> 16:03.374
<i>Just pretend SpongeBob is me.</i>

16:03.389 --> 16:06.310
And instead of having amazing
adventures under the sea,

16:06.325 --> 16:08.212
he's sorry
he insulted his family.

16:08.227 --> 16:11.548
You don't understand.
We're never getting past this.

16:11.610 --> 16:15.445
Okay. I knew there was a small
chance the cake wouldn't work.

16:15.460 --> 16:18.121
But maybe you'll find
this filling more persuasive.

16:18.261 --> 16:20.350
You're all coming with me
to the C.I.A.

16:20.381 --> 16:22.426
We have another memory eraser,
and I'm gonna use it

16:22.437 --> 16:24.561
to make you forget
all the things I said...

16:24.607 --> 16:27.481
and the so-called "gun incident."

16:27.634 --> 16:29.433
There's another memory eraser?!

16:29.484 --> 16:32.307
That might be the only way
we can be a family again.

16:32.482 --> 16:33.971
I think you can
put down the gun, Dad.

16:34.012 --> 16:35.205
We all want to forget.

16:35.254 --> 16:36.820
<i>Roger: Ow!</i>

16:39.464 --> 16:42.479
Bad news... We sold
the other memory neutralizer.

16:42.546 --> 16:43.493
No!

16:43.495 --> 16:45.015
Wait.
What's in the box, then?

16:45.030 --> 16:46.897
Lil' Angelo!

16:47.967 --> 16:50.921
Oh, yeah, you missed
the C.I.A. mascot elections.

16:50.991 --> 16:53.640
Gretchen the Guinea Pig ran
a tight race, but I think

16:53.655 --> 16:56.760
we're still a ways off from
electing a female mascot.

16:56.800 --> 16:58.562
Dick, do you know who bought
the other neutralizer?

16:58.616 --> 17:00.397
Yeah. Got the receipt right here.

17:00.412 --> 17:03.534
- Some C.I.A. collector in Ohio.
- Ohio?!

17:03.578 --> 17:05.935
B-But we only have 24 hours
from when you said those things

17:06.016 --> 17:08.606
- to get there!
- Yeah, If we don't make it by morning,

17:08.826 --> 17:11.442
we're gonna remember
all the crap you said forever!

17:11.619 --> 17:12.990
All the jokes.

17:16.126 --> 17:19.016
Look, I know I hurt you guys,
but let me make it up to you.

17:19.327 --> 17:21.484
Just because this is a day
that you're all going to forget

17:21.500 --> 17:23.704
doesn't mean it can't be
a day to remember.

17:23.720 --> 17:24.454
And then forget.

17:24.547 --> 17:26.490
Can you just shut up
and focus on driving?

17:26.505 --> 17:27.992
- Yep.
- Driving's pretty cool.

17:28.204 --> 17:30.194
You, uh, want to give it
a try, son?

17:30.217 --> 17:32.069
- What?
- Yeah, you'll be driving soon.

17:32.084 --> 17:32.984
Stan, leave him alone.

17:33.084 --> 17:35.432
What? I'm doing something
nice... father/son.

17:35.447 --> 17:36.700
Here, take the wheel.

17:37.566 --> 17:38.802
Aah!

17:40.181 --> 17:42.039
It's just like
one of your video games...

17:42.133 --> 17:44.041
the ultimate video game.

17:44.076 --> 17:47.277
You only have one life...
well, technically, four lives.

17:47.337 --> 17:48.953
Whoop! Guardrail.

17:52.462 --> 17:54.118
Please tell me you can fix this.

17:54.137 --> 17:55.786
What makes you think
I can fix...

17:55.801 --> 17:58.956
Oh. 'Cause of the tow truck
and the coveralls.

17:58.971 --> 18:02.706
No, no, no, I'm not a mechanic.
I'm just a strange man.

18:07.346 --> 18:08.599
Guys, we got one!

18:08.614 --> 18:10.424
Everybody, thumbs out
and look sexy.

18:10.524 --> 18:12.547
We don't know who this is
or what they're into.

18:17.083 --> 18:20.757
The mouse can never resist
the cheese.

18:21.393 --> 18:23.347
Hey.

18:23.469 --> 18:27.116
- Hey. Hey.
- What?

18:27.331 --> 18:30.354
What's your record
for Tylenol PMs?

18:30.426 --> 18:33.557
- What do you mean?
- What's the most you've ever taken?

18:33.834 --> 18:35.292
I've done seven.

18:35.795 --> 18:37.761
Stan, I think it's your turn
to ride shotgun!

18:37.931 --> 18:41.013
Nonsense. My queen
always rides in front.

18:43.209 --> 18:44.681
Hey.

18:48.318 --> 18:49.886
Eight.

18:53.212 --> 18:55.979
Hey. Hey.
We're good.

18:56.053 --> 18:58.693
The place we're going
is just right up here.

18:59.458 --> 19:02.866
One more... right here.

19:04.369 --> 19:05.869
27.

19:11.913 --> 19:13.664
Let me just say thanks
to our friend.

19:13.679 --> 19:15.676
He's dead.
We have 10 minutes.

19:18.801 --> 19:21.488
Don't get many visitors,
but I'm always happy

19:21.518 --> 19:23.733
to show off
my C.I.A. memorabilia.

19:23.748 --> 19:25.584
Whoa!
Hayley, check it out!

19:25.611 --> 19:27.724
The super crack we introduced
in the '80s.

19:28.127 --> 19:31.502
Look! Steve!
The real Jason Bourne!

19:33.424 --> 19:35.780
How do I know how to do this?!

19:35.831 --> 19:38.264
Dad!
We only have four minutes!

19:38.343 --> 19:40.524
I believe this is
what you came for.

19:40.600 --> 19:42.460
Now let's talk about a fair price.

19:45.493 --> 19:46.951
Okay, we only got 30 seconds.

19:47.051 --> 19:48.765
I'll just zap you,
and we can forget

19:48.787 --> 19:50.934
about the worst day of our lives.

19:51.053 --> 19:54.448
You know, I... I meant
what I wrote on the cake.

19:54.775 --> 19:57.971
"Bad dad... sad."

19:58.777 --> 20:00.991
Aah! That's hot!

20:01.006 --> 20:02.746
Steve, that was our last chance.

20:02.761 --> 20:06.576
I can't believe I'm saying this,
but we shouldn't forget this day.

20:06.628 --> 20:09.215
Right! Because we made all these great

20:09.227 --> 20:11.755
new memories today... as a family!

20:11.843 --> 20:13.924
And that's the true meaning
of Father's Day.

20:13.939 --> 20:16.627
Are you kidding me?!
Today was a disaster!

20:16.642 --> 20:19.896
Well...
but, then... I'm screwed.

20:19.957 --> 20:21.493
You're gonna hate me forever.

20:21.593 --> 20:23.834
Yeah, we want you to feel
that way 'cause you've been

20:23.901 --> 20:26.403
working your ass off all day
to make things right.

20:26.418 --> 20:28.605
It turns out the only thing
that makes you a good dad

20:28.620 --> 20:31.241
- is being a guilty dad.
- Yeah.

20:31.317 --> 20:33.659
And that's the true meaning
of Father's Day.

20:33.693 --> 20:36.762
- No!!
- That's just a character flaw!

20:36.782 --> 20:40.089
Noticing my flaws
and my strengths.

20:40.137 --> 20:42.234
Is... that the true meaning
of Father's Day?

20:42.249 --> 20:44.570
Dad, I'll explain it all in
the back of that guy's pickup.

20:44.585 --> 20:47.005
Or better yet...
why don't you drive?

20:47.672 --> 20:48.507
<i>You know what, guys?</i>

20:48.522 --> 20:51.710
<i>This is easily one
of my favorite Father's Days.</i>

20:51.782 --> 20:52.744
<i>And Christmases.</i>

20:53.035 --> 20:54.771
<i>Did you guys know
it was Christmas?</i>

